==English==

===Etymology===
From {{term|under}} + {{term|bridge}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{British}} A [[bridge]] that allows traffic to pass [[under]] a [[road]], [[river]], [[railway]] etc.

====Usage notes====
Where a bridge takes one form of transport over another it is both an underbridge and an [[overbridge]], depending on the reference level. For example, where a road passes above a railway, the bridge is an overbridge from the point of view of the road, and an underbridge from the point of view of the railway.

